One possible modification is to introduce a different activation function instead of ReLU for the first FC layer. For example, using GELU or Swish might provide better non-linear modeling capabilities without increasing computational complexity significantly.

Another idea is to add dropout layers between the FC layers to prevent overfitting, especially when dealing with smaller datasets or models prone to memorization.

